{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Update the Health and Safety at Work Act to be gender neutral",
        "additional_details": "By replacing words like \u201chis\u201d with \u201ctheir,\u201d I think the Government can encourage a sense of respect and belonging for all. As the Employment Rights Bill will aim to strengthen measures on sexual harassment prevention, many are shocked to see how exclusionary this language remains in the Health and Safety at Work Act. I believe updating the Act would be a meaningful step towards greater inclusivity.",
        "background": "I believe this law uses outdated gendered language like \u201chis employees\u201d, and that it should be updated to be more inclusive as it applies to everyone regardless of their gender. I believe updating this language would reflect the UK\u2019s commitment to fairness, equality, and respect for all workers. ",
